ABOUT THE FILM
Beginning of the XVIII century. Cartographer Jonathan Green commits a scientific journey from Europe to the East. Proceeding through Transylvania and the Carpathian Mountains overcome, he falls into the lost village of impenetrable forests. Only the will of the case and thick fog could bring him to this cursed place. The people living here do not like any kind of traveler hitherto. These people have to fend for themselves from the rest of the world by a deep moat, naively believe that they can protect themselves from evil, not realizing that it has long been settled in their hearts, and only waiting for the case to escape. Even in a nightmare materialistic scientists had no idea that he is destined to meet with a faithful servant of the devil.
